The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Annual concert
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                          Annual concert
                                          
	Annual concert        
	Indus Valley World school staged its first annual concert at Madhusudan Mancha in the last week of December, with dancer Piyali Ray and Moulik D. Berkana, deputy director of American Center, as guests of honour.        
	The primary and middle school students showcased the various stages of mankinds evolution, starting from the primitive times to the modern era. Students also performed to the Jodha Akbar song Azeem-o-shan, shahenshah. A fusion dance on the theme, Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam, meaning the whole world in one family, brought the programme to an end.        
	Said the principal-director of the school, Usha Mehta: All credit for todays programme goes to the students who worked to make the day a success.         
	Patriotic songs        
	Shaw Public School organised an inter-school patriotic song competition on February 4. The judges were musicians Neel Dutt and Soumya Shankar Roy. Shambo Dutta, a Class VII student of National Gems School sang Ei banglar mati to win in the solo category. The National Gems team were declared winners. A KE Carmel School team sang Jodi tor dak shune keu to be declared runner-up.        
	IBM Quizzit        
	In the February 16 report, Brain-teasers for thought, it should have been mentioned that the quiz contest, Quizzit was presented by IBM, in association with Texas Instruments and International School of Business, Calcutta, as part of Infocom 2009-10. The error is regretted.                                                                                                                                                      
